name: NSFastEnumeration
desc: A protocol that objects adopt to support fast enumeration.

items.name: func countByEnumerating(with: UnsafeMutablePointer<NSFastEnumerationState>, objects: AutoreleasingUnsafeMutablePointer<AnyObject?>, count: Int) -> Int
items.desc: Returns by reference a C array of objects over which the sender should iterate, and as the return value the number of objects in the array.

items.name: struct NSFastEnumerationState
items.desc: This defines the structure used as contextual information in the NSFastEnumeration protocol.
